Package org.atlanmod.commons.function

Interface BiConverter<T,​U,​R>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the first argument to the converter
    U - the type of the second argument to the converter
    R - the type of the result of the converter
    All Superinterfaces:
    BiFunction<T,​U,​R>
    @ParametersAreNonnullByDefault
public interface BiConverter<T,​U,​R>
extends BiFunction<T,​U,​R>
    A specialized BiFunction that converts an object of type T to another of type R, by using an object of type U.

    The reverse operation may be strict inverse, meaning that converter.revert(converter.convert(a, c), c).equals(a) always true.

    See Also:
    BiFunction
